                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">662.6331/86: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 6, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Legation’s 30, April 4, 1 p.m. Are “interim duties” temporary duties which
                    will be imposed at the Austro-German border until the customs union is
                    completely organized? Do you know when they will go into effect or what they
                    will be?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
